    "sections": [
        {
            "heading": "Burp MCP + Codex CLI Integration",
            "subheadings": [
                {
                    "heading": "Overview & Benefits",
                    "type": "list",
                    "content": [
                        "**Passive Discovery**: Automatically find vulnerabilities during manual exploration.",
                        "**IDOR & Logic Flaws**: Codex reasons over traffic to identify auth bypasses and SSRF.",
                        "**No API Keys**: Full local control over your data and interception stack.",
                        "**Evidence-Based Reporting**: Generate reports directly from real Burp HTTP history."
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "heading": "1. Server Installation",
                    "type": "image",
                    "src": "/gitbook/assets/image.png",
                    "caption": "Extract the MCP server proxy JAR from the Burp Suite BApp Store extension tab."
                },
                {
                    "heading": "2. Codex & Caddy Configuration",
                    "type": "code_block",
                    "content": [
                        "# ~/.codex/config.toml configuration",
                        "[mcp_servers.burp]",
                        "command = \"java\"",
                        "args = [\"-jar\", \"/path/to/mcp-proxy.jar\", \"--sse-url\", \"http://127.0.0.1:19876\"]",
                        "",
                        "# Reverse Proxy (Caddyfile) for Origin validation workaround",
                        ":19876",
                        "reverse_proxy 127.0.0.1:9876 {",
                        "  header_up Host \"127.0.0.1:9876\"",
                        "  header_up Origin \"http://127.0.0.1:9876\"",
                        "  header_up -User-Agent",
                        "  header_up -Accept",
                        "}"
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "heading": "3. Verification",
                    "type": "image",
                    "src": "/gitbook/assets/image (1).png",
                    "caption": "Verify the MCP server status using the /mcp command in Codex."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "heading": "Operational Tips & Optimization",
            "subheadings": [
                {
                    "heading": "Configuration Best Practices",
                    "type": "list",
                    "content": [
                        "**Scope Management**: Use `.*\\.test\\.com$` to include all subdomains in the project scope.",
                        "**Noise Reduction**: Configure TLS Pass Through for common domains like `google.com` and `mozilla.com`.",
                        "**Redirections**: Enable JavaScript-driven redirections in Project Options -> HTTP.",
                        "**Interception**: Keep Proxy Interception 'Always disabled' in User Options for smoother workflow."
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "heading": "Troubleshooting Burp Stability",
                    "type": "code_block",
                    "content": [
                        "# Fix unprivileged user namespace clone (Linux)",
                        "sudo sysctl -w kernel.unprivileged_userns_clone=1",
                        "",
                        "# Fix chrome-sandbox permissions for embedded browser",
                        "find .BurpSuite -name chrome-sandbox -exec chown root:root {} \\; -exec chmod 4755 {} \\;"
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "heading": "Advanced Attack & Extension Suite",
            "subheadings": [
                {
